---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  eyebrow="Hobart LXeR · CMA Energy Mizer · Champion UH-150 · Jackson Conserver"
  title="Undercounter Commercial Dishwasher Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle="Bars, cafés, small restaurants across LA, OC, Ventura, Riverside. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Same-day dispatch. No emergency surcharge."
  heroImageTitle="Undercounter Commercial Dishwasher Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Undercounter commercial dishwashers, 30 to 40 racks an hour.</h2>

    <p>Undercounter commercial dishwashers fit under bar counter or café prep counter, 30 to 40 racks per hour throughput. Bars, cafés, small restaurants, mobile kitchens. NSF 184 commercial rating distinguishes them from residential undercounters: 208V or 240V three-phase electrical, faster cycles (90 seconds to 4 minutes), higher wash temps, integrated chemical sanitizing or high-temp final rinse.</p>

    <p>Four platforms dominate LA bar and café installs: <strong>Hobart UH series and LXeR</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group, the most common premium undercounter), <strong>CMA Energy Mizer</strong> (Cleveland-based commercial dishwasher specialist), <strong>Champion UH-150</strong> (Ali Group, sister brand to Scotsman ice and Beverage-Air refrigeration), <strong>Jackson Conserver</strong> (Hoshizaki America acquired). Plus Insinger Speeder on legacy installs.</p>

    <p>BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair, no emergency surcharge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Typical undercounter failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Six failure modes account for most undercounter calls.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Door gasket compression (year 4 to 7).</strong> Bar undercounters open and close 200+ times per shift. Gasket compresses, door switch interlock fails. Replacement $200 to $360 per unit installed.</li>
      <li><strong>Wash pump impeller wear.</strong> Mineral scale plus glass shards plus organic debris erode impeller blades. Wash coverage drops, dishes come out dirty. $360 to $540 part plus labor.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain pump.</strong> Bar service produces a lot of pulp, cherry stems, lemon peels. Drain pump impeller and check valve fail at year 4 to 6. $300 to $480.</li>
      <li><strong>Detergent dispenser solenoid.</strong> Chemical detergent (Auto-Chlor, Ecolab) corrodes solenoid coil over time. Cycle runs without proper detergent dose. $260 to $400.</li>
      <li><strong>Booster heater (smaller capacity than rack-conveyor scale).</strong> Final rinse 180°F NSF compliance. Element burnout less frequent than larger units but still happens at year 6 to 9. $620 to $920.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve.</strong> Hard-water mineral scale degrades the valve diaphragm. Cycle starts with insufficient water. $280 to $440.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent jobs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>West Hollywood · Hobart LXeR cocktail bar undercounter, 6 years old</h3>
      <p>Wash coverage uneven, glassware spotting. Diagnosed: wash pump impeller worn from glass shard erosion (typical bar service). Replaced impeller, cleaned wash arm jets, tested 5 cycles. Total: $120 plus $260 part plus 1 hour = $480.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pasadena · CMA Energy Mizer café undercounter, 8 years old</h3>
      <p>Multi-issue at year 8: drain pump slow, door gasket compressed flat. Replaced drain pump and door gasket on single visit. Total: $120 plus $320 parts plus 1.5 hours = $560.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · Champion UH-150 restaurant undercounter, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Final rinse at 168°F, NSF needs 180°F. Booster heater element open. Replaced element, descaled rinse arm, verified 184°F. Total: $120 plus $480 part plus 1.5 hours = $720.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Burbank · Jackson Conserver hotel pantry undercounter, 5 years old</h3>
      <p>Cycle stopping short, error code on detergent fault. Diagnosed: detergent dispenser solenoid corroded, intermittent activation. Replaced solenoid, calibrated detergent feed rate. Total: $120 plus $290 part plus 1 hour = $440.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Long Beach · Hobart LXeR brewery taproom undercounter, 4 years old</h3>
      <p>Water inlet running long, cycle starts thin. Diagnosed: water inlet valve diaphragm degraded from hard water. Replaced valve, ran 3 verification cycles. Total: $120 plus $310 part plus 1 hour = $460.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for undercounter, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hobart UH series and LXeR, CMA Energy Mizer, Champion UH-150, Jackson Conserver, Insinger Speeder. Both high-temp final rinse (NSF 180°F) and chemical sanitizing variants. Door gaskets, wash pumps, drain pumps, detergent and rinse aid dispensers, booster heaters, water inlet valves, control boards.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new undercounter installation under custom bar millwork (cabinetmaker / fabricator trade); chemical supply contracts (Ecolab, Auto-Chlor, Diversey); residential dishwasher service on this page (different scope, different diagnostic tier).</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What undercounter dishwasher repair actually costs.</h2>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement</td><td>$200 to $360</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wash pump impeller</td><td>$440 to $640</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drain pump</td><td>$380 to $560</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Detergent dispenser solenoid</td><td>$320 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Booster heater element</td><td>$620 to $920</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water inlet valve</td><td>$340 to $520</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Control board replacement</td><td>$540 to $820</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$700 to $1,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="price-note">$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. No emergency surcharge. Bar undercounters often pair with under-bar ice machines, we handle both on the same dispatch.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Brands we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Four undercounter platforms cover most LA bars and cafés.</h2>

    <p><strong>Hobart</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group): UH series and LXeR. Premium undercounter, the most-deployed brand in LA. See <a href="/brands/hobart-dishwasher-repair/">Hobart commercial dishwasher repair</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>CMA</strong> (Cleveland-based commercial dishwasher specialist): Energy Mizer line. Common in cafés and small restaurants. See <a href="/brands/cma-dishmachines-repair/">CMA commercial dish machine repair</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Champion</strong> (Ali Group): UH-150. Mid-premium, common in chain operations. See <a href="/brands/champion-dishwasher-repair/">Champion commercial dishwasher repair</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Jackson</strong> (Hoshizaki America acquired): Conserver line. Strong post-acquisition parts availability. See <a href="/brands/jackson-dishwasher-repair/">Jackson commercial dishwasher repair</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Meiko</strong> (German engineering, separate company): less common in LA bar segment but premium quality on hospitality and gastro-pub installs. See <a href="/brands/meiko-dishwasher-repair/">Meiko commercial dishwasher repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Eight reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Bar service hour awareness.</strong> Friday and Saturday evenings are our highest undercounter call volume. We dispatch around your service.</li>
      <li><strong>Common parts on the van.</strong> Door gaskets, wash pump impellers, drain pumps, detergent dispensers for Hobart LXeR, CMA Energy Mizer, Champion UH-150.</li>
      <li><strong>Glass shard expertise.</strong> Bar wash pumps see glass damage that café and small-restaurant pumps don't. We diagnose for it.</li>
      <li><strong>NSF 180°F final rinse verification</strong> for high-temp variants. Chemical sanitizing variant compliance also documented.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering, no emergency surcharge.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Bar dispatch combo.</strong> Undercounter dishwasher and under-bar ice machine on the same visit when both need work.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/rack-conveyor-dishwasher-repair/">rack conveyor</a>, <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/flight-type-dishwasher-repair/">flight type</a>, <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/glass-washer-repair/">glass washer</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/">commercial dishwasher repair</a>. Credentials: <a href="/credentials/licensed/">BHGS license</a>, <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Undercounter dishwasher repair, common questions.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
          <p>{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bottom-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Undercounter Down? Call Us 24/7.</h2>
    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura. No emergency surcharge. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-primary">☎ Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .section { padding: 72px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .container.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 20px; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--text); letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 24px; font-style: italic; }
